Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, 1 tsp @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp}
(2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> You'll use the rest of the Southwest Spice Blend later.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in asparagus for potatoes; roast @?asparagus{6%ounce} for ~{10-12%minutes}.
> Save potatoes for another use.

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and very thinly slice ¼ of the
@red onion{1}; finely chop remaining. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve
@brioche buns{2}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the
lime (use the rest of the lime as you like), @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4
servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Microwave until onion is softened,
~{1%minute}. Set aside.

In a second small bowl, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{1%unit},
@mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} (all for
4 servings), remaining @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, and 1 TBSP
@water{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chopped onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground plant-based protein{6%ounce}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed,
until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned and warmed
through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add 2 TBSP @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) to pan with plant-based
protein, then stir in BBQ sauce mixture. Cook, stirring, until sauce has
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off
heat.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add another splash of water.

Meanwhile, toast buns until golden brown.

Divide buns between plates; spread cut sides of bottom buns with
@vegan chipotle mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Fill buns with messy jane filling and
as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Serve with potato wedges on
the side and any remaining mayo for dipping.

> Ground Plant-Based Protein is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.